h travelers.San Francisco International Airport (SFO)San FranciscoUnited States18 min11 miOakland International Airport (OAK)OaklandUnited States26 min11 miSan Jose Mineta International Airport (SJC)San JoseUnited States51 min39 miSacramento International Airport (SMF)SacramentoUnited States1 hr 33 min78 miPopular airports near ChicagoClose dialogDistance and driving time are relative to the city center. Airports are listed based on distance from Chicago center and popularity with travelers.Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD)ChicagoUnited States24 min16 miChicago Midway International Airport (MDW)ChicagoUnited States22 min9 miMilwaukee Mitchell International Airport (MKE)MilwaukeeUnited States1 hr 22 min75 miIndianapolis International Airport (IND)IndianapolisUnited States2 hr 55 min165 miFrequently asked questions about flying from San Francisco to Chicago  How long does it take to fly from San Francisco to Chicago?4 hr is the shortest flight time from San Francisco to Chicago.When are the cheapest days to fly from San Francisco to Chicago?The cheapest days to fly are usually in  September. Typical prices range from $125 to $200.Which airlines provide the cheapest flights from San Francisco to Chicago?The best round-trip deal recently found on Google Flights from San Francisco to Chicago was with United from $179. The best one-way deal was with Alaska from $90.Some of the cheapest round-trip deals we found with different airlines:The cheapest United round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $179, flying from Aug 7 to Aug 13.The cheapest American round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $179, flying from Aug 8 to Aug 14.The cheapest Southwest round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $199, flying from Aug 21 to Aug 27.The cheapest Delta round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $257, flying from Aug 21 to Aug 29.The cheapest Alaska round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $188, flying from Aug 9 to Aug 15.The cheapest Frontier round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $238, flying from Aug 21 to Aug 27.What is the best airline to fly from San Francisco to Chicago?What counts as the best airline for your flights from San Francisco  to Chicago really depends on your individual needs.  You may have a favorite carrier or a loyalty program you like, but price, convenience, and airports served also come into play. Flexibility and booking terms – Can you change flights if you want to stay longer or get a refund if you have to postpone your trip? – are also factors that help determine which airline is best to fly from San Francisco  to Chicago.In terms of nonstop flights, United is the most popular. United offers 72 nonstop flights and 597 connecting flights per week. United flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).In terms of flights, Southwest is the most popular. Southwest offers 7 nonstop flights and 1,922 connecting flights per week. Southwest flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago Midway International Airport (MDW), Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).Other popular airlines flying from San Francisco to Chicago are:American offers 41 nonstop flights and 233 connecting flights per week. American flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).Delta offers 543 connecting flights per week. Delta flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago Midway International Airport (MDW), Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).Alaska offers 7 nonstop flights and 55 connecting flights per week. Alaska flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).Frontier offers 56 connecting flights per week. Frontier flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago Midway International Airport (MDW), Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).The number of connecting fligh