apest Frontier round-trip flight from San Francisco to Chicago is $238, flying from Aug 21 to Aug 27.What is the best airline to fly from San Francisco to Chicago?What counts as the best airline for your flights from San Francisco  to Chicago really depends on your individual needs.  You may have a favorite carrier or a loyalty program you like, but price, convenience, and airports served also come into play. Flexibility and booking terms – Can you change flights if you want to stay longer or get a refund if you have to postpone your trip? – are also factors that help determine which airline is best to fly from San Francisco  to Chicago.In terms of nonstop flights, United is the most popular. United offers 72 nonstop flights and 597 connecting flights per week. United flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).In terms of flights, Southwest is the most popular. Southwest offers 7 nonstop flights and 1,922 connecting flights per week. Southwest flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago Midway International Airport (MDW), Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).Other popular airlines flying from San Francisco to Chicago are:American offers 41 nonstop flights and 233 connecting flights per week. American flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).Delta offers 543 connecting flights per week. Delta flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago Midway International Airport (MDW), Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).Alaska offers 7 nonstop flights and 55 connecting flights per week. Alaska flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).Frontier offers 56 connecting flights per week. Frontier flies from San Francisco International Airport (SFO) to Chicago Midway International Airport (MDW), Chicago O'Hare International Airport (ORD).The number of connecting fligh